import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of price?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Price")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_price_by_symbol = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=avg_price_by_symbol)
    plt.title('What is the average price by symbol?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Symbol')
    plt.ylabel('Average Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['symbol_count'] = data.groupby('symbol')['symbol'].transform('count')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='symbol_count', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of symbols?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Symbol')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Symbols', loc='upper right', labels=data['symbol'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
